   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FIFTY-TWO THE CHURCH AS GOD'S DWELLING</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>FOR HIS CORPORATE EXPRESSION THE LORD'S DAY MORNING MESSAGE 2</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Date:10:00 a.m., The Lord's Day, April 18, 1948</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Place:Hardoon Road, Shanghai</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Speaker:Chen Keh-san, Witness Lee</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Prayer: Lord, unless the Holy Spirit brings these words into the depths of our spirit, what we speak is vain.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>We can do nothing.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>What we need is Your presence.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Only the operation of the Holy Spirit will bring about Your work.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Lord, we are gathered together in Your Name.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>You are surely with us.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>If we give Your light the ground, You will surely shine on us.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>You will surely cause us to touch You.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>We pray that You will stop Satan from occupying any ground in man's mind.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Scripture Reading: Isa 57:15; Matt 1:21-24; Eph 3:17; 2:22; 1:23; 3:10; Rev 1:5b-6; Eph 5:25; Matt 16:18-19 THE CHURCH</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>GOD'S DWELLING PLACE IN SPIRIT God Becoming a Man to Dwell among Men</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Brother Chen Keh-san:God dwells in the most high place.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>As far as space is concerned, He dwells "in the high and holy place" Isa 57:15 .</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>As far as time is concerned, He "inhabits eternity."</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In terms of space, when one reaches the highest place, he reaches God's dwelling.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Airplanes can only fly as high as ten thousand feet or thirty thousand feet; they can go no higher.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>But God dwells in the highest place.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>He is also the One who exists from eternity to eternity.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>He is like a circle that has no beginning or ending.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The wonderful thing is that this God who dwells in eternity one day came to earth to become a man and to dwell among men.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>His name was Emmanuel Matt 1:21-24 .</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>The Pharisees asked when the kingdom of God was coming Luke 17:20 .</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>They were the hypocrites.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The Lord could not say to them that the kingdom of God is in their hearts.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Their hearts were full of dead bones.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>The Lord is the King of the kingdom of the heavens.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Yet He dwells among men.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Where the Lord is, there is the kingdom.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>This is why the Lord says that the kingdom of God was among them Luke 17:21 .</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>This means that the Lord was among them.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>God in Christ Dwelling in the Church</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Christ was in the flesh for only a few dozen years.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>After He died and resurrected, He produced the church.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>The producing of the church can be likened to the producing of Eve out of Adam.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>When the Holy Spirit came, He dwells within the believers and also within the church.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>Today, God dwells among us through the Holy Spirit, and here we have the church.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>At the same time, the church becomes the dwelling place of God Eph 2:22 .</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>All the fullness of the Godhead dwells bodily in Christ Col 2:9 .</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>Everything in Christ is everything of God.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>Christ is like a bank, and God is like the deposits in the bank.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>If Christ "goes under," God will become poor.</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>Suppose I put my watch, my pen, and all my money into this handkerchief.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>Either you take the whole thing, or you get nothing.</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>This is God's way.</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>God does not give fragments to man; He gives the whole thing to man.</S>
   <S PAR='51' RSNT='1' SNO='51'>When a man receives Christ, he receives life, forgiveness, and so forth.</S>
   <S PAR='52' RSNT='1' SNO='52'>If he does not want Christ, he will have nothing.</S>
   <S PAR='53' RSNT='1' SNO='53'>Today, when we believe in Christ, we receive all the riches.</S>
   <S PAR='54' RSNT='1' SNO='54'>Everything is in Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='55' RSNT='1' SNO='55'>With Christ, we have everything.</S>
   <S PAR='56' RSNT='1' SNO='56'>Without Him, we have nothing.</S>
   <S PAR='57' RSNT='1' SNO='57'>When I have the sunlight, I do not need the little flashes of the torchlight any longer.</S>
   <S PAR='58' RSNT='1' SNO='58'>Today, God's glory dwells in Christ, and Christ is in us.</S>
   <S PAR='59' RSNT='1' SNO='59'>What can be more glorious than this?</S>
   <S PAR='60' RSNT='1' SNO='60'>Even if the head of a nation were to walk with us, that glory would not be a glory when compared with the glory of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='61' RSNT='1' SNO='61'>On the contrary, it will become a shame.</S>
   </TEXT>
